Key Entry Points and Architectural Patterns
•	Entry point: cli.py → main() function
•	Architecture: Layered — cli → task_manager → storage → tasks.json
•	Shared blueprint: models.py used across all layers
•	No external dependencies — entirely self-contained Python

Key Components and Their Responsibilities
Component	Responsibility
cli.py	Receives user commands and passes them to task_manager
task_manager.py	Applies business rules — create, update, delete, filter tasks
models.py	Defines Task blueprint with all fields and allowed statuses/priorities
storage.py	Reads and writes task data to tasks.json on disk
task_priority.py	Calculates importance scores and sorts tasks by urgency
task_parser.py	Parses free-form text into structured Task objects
task_list_merge.py	Combines two separate task lists into one unified list

